	<p class="bodyTitle">
		Medicaid and CHIP in Puerto Rico
	</p>
	<div class="blueBox">
		<p class="bodyText">
			Medicaid which includes the Children's Health Insurance Program (CHIP) provides health and long-term care coverage to some people with limited income, including children and parents, pregnant women, people with disabilities, and seniors.
			In Puerto Rico, this health insurance is provided through managed care Health Plans that have contracts with the Government of Puerto Rico.The program is called "Mi Salud," formally "Reforma."
		</p>
	</div>
