			<p class="bodySubTitle">Who Can Apply?</p>
			<p class="bodyText">
				Everyone residing in Puerto Rico is entitled to apply voluntarily in order to be evaluated at the local offices.
				Eligibility for Medicaid is based on your resident's status, family income, resources and other factors. 
				Therefore, it is necessary that the family or individual applying for assistance have the proper documents available at the time of the appointment to avoid any delays in determining your eligibility.
				These documents must provide proof of citizenship and age, monthly income and resources.
			</p>
			<div class="dottedLine"></div>
			<p class="bodySubTitle">Where Can I Apply?</p>
			<p class="bodyText">
				Applications for Medicaid can be filled out at the Oficina Local de Programa de Asistencia M&eacute;dica (Local Office of Medical Assistance) in the town where the person or family resides.
				Some towns have more than one local office.Office hours are from 7:00 am to 3:30 pm.
			</p><br />
			<p class="bodyText">
				The person must go to the local town office where they reside and request an appointment (appointments are not given over the phone).
				The appointment is given after a preliminary interview is conducted the same day that the person applies.
				In order to be evaluated and determine eligibility, the person must then return to the office on the appointed day with the documents that were requested in the preliminary interview. 
			</p>
